lines to help fuse Italian operatic melodies and brass traditions with African rhythms; this
development played a pivotal role in the creation of the world-renowned genre of jazz; and
WHEREAS, the heritage of Italy is found in the timeless art, the enduring strength
of the Italian-American community, and the profound influence of Italian culture on the
unique fabric of Louisiana life.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commemorate the celebration of St. Joseph's Day on
Thursday, March 19, 2026, and does hereby recognize the cultural and historic links between
Italy and Louisiana.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the House of Representatives does hereby
establish the Italian American Legislative Caucus of the Legislature of Louisiana to
represent and speak for Louisiana's Italian American citizens and to preserve and promote
the traditions of citizens of Italian heritage.
SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
